| **Length** | One phrase, name, number, or title | “The answer is X”, “It is X” |
| **Formatting** | Matches punctuation and space usage | “Back–to‑back”, “converted to” |
| **Case** | Lowercase “yes”/“no” for binary | “Yes”, “No” |
| **Suffix** | No trailing punctuation unless part of the answer | “yes.” |

8. **Edge Cases**  
   - **Dates**: Include the full date range if it appears (e.g., “October 1922”).  
   - **Titles**: Include the full title if the context uses it (e.g., “Chief of Protocol”).  
   - **Names with titles**: Use the exact form from the text (“William Jefferson Clinton”).  

Follow these generalized principles to produce concise, accurate, and compliant HotpotQA answers.
